with your left foot a lot.

205
00:11:04,798 --> 00:11:06,098
Yeah.
- How are you?

206
00:11:06,166 --> 00:11:08,934
Okay. I mean, it's B team,
so it's mostly 'tards.

207
00:11:09,002 --> 00:11:11,804
Well, better to be a big
fish in a small pond.

208
00:11:11,871 --> 00:11:14,206
Even if all the other fish
are 'tard fish?

209
00:11:14,274 --> 00:11:18,644
Yeah. Even then.

210
00:11:18,712 --> 00:11:20,346
I, uh...

211
00:11:20,413 --> 00:11:22,181
I should stop here.

212
00:11:22,248 --> 00:11:24,383
When are you coming back?

213
00:11:24,451 --> 00:11:26,952
Well, it'll be sooner
than last time.

214
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:28,320
Probably a couple of weeks.

215
00:11:28,388 --> 00:11:29,588
Two weeks?

216
00:11:29,656 --> 00:11:31,123
Probably three.
- No, four.

217
00:11:31,191 --> 00:11:32,491
No, definitely not four.

218
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:34,059
But send me
letters, okay?

219
00:11:34,127 --> 00:11:35,627
Okay.

220
00:11:40,367 --> 00:11:42,401
Okay.

221
00:11:44,904 --> 00:11:46,572
Keep your nose
clean, kid.

222
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:48,574
Okay.

223
00:11:48,641 --> 00:11:51,377
Okay. I love you, Gulls.

224
00:11:51,444 --> 00:11:52,578
Me, too.

225
00:11:52,645 --> 00:11:54,213
Mm. Okay.

226
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:55,514
Now, go on.

227
00:11:55,582 --> 00:11:56,682
(sniffles)

228
00:11:56,750 --> 00:11:57,983
I'll see you soon, okay?

229
00:11:58,051 --> 00:11:59,218
Couple of weeks?

230
00:11:59,285 --> 00:12:00,386
Yeah, a couple.

231
00:12:00,453 --> 00:12:01,720
And try reading that
<i>Johnny</i>, uh,

232
00:12:01,788 --> 00:12:03,856
what's-his-face book
one more time, okay?

233
00:12:03,923 --> 00:12:05,891
I can't, Mom.
I swear, it's horrible.

234
00:12:05,959 --> 00:12:07,092
(laughs)

235
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:09,228
Forget it. Forget it.

236
00:12:09,295 --> 00:12:11,030
Go on, don't be late.

237
00:12:11,097 --> 00:12:13,098
Okay.

238
00:12:34,354 --> 00:12:35,521
